id: pm-hl9y
title: "GH-284: align pm init required schema directories with health"
description: "GitHub issue #284 reports pm init followed by pm health can warn that required schema directories show-types and types are missing. Reproduce current behavior, align init/health directory requirements if needed, add regression coverage, and close the GitHub issue through the PR."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:health","area:init","area:schema","github:284"
created_at: "2026-06-18T13:16:38.873Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-18T13:45:56.153Z"
author: codex-sdk-cli-continuation
parent: pm-8jdc
resolution: "Custom schema item types now create their required storage folders during schema registration, and rerunning pm init repairs folders for schema-defined types that predate the fix."
expected_result: pm health should not report missing required directories after pm schema add-type/apply-preset/infer or after rerunning pm init on a tracker with schema-defined custom item types.
actual_result: "Focused tests, manual temp smoke, linked pm tests, and full 100% coverage confirmed missing custom type directories are created or repaired and health returns ok."
